  <data key="d14">ann.concept-dissimulation-contrary-to-concept-truth-self-presentation-st-ii-ii-q111-a001-resp</data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q111.a001.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">ardly by outward signs to be such as one is. Now outward signs are not only words, but also deeds . Accordingly just as it is contrary to truth to signify by words something different from that which is in one's mind, so also is it contrary to truth to employ signs of deeds or things to signify the con</data>
  <data key="d18">reviewed_doctrinal</data>
  <data key="d19">self_presentation</data>
</edge>
