  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q111.a001.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">ings to signify the contrary of what is in oneself, and this is what is properly denoted by dissimulation. Consequently dissimulation is properly a lie told by the signs of outward deeds . Now it matters not whether one lie in word or in any other way, as stated above ( II-II:110:1 Objection 2 ). Wherefore, si</data>
  <data key="d18">reviewed_doctrinal</data>
  <data key="d19">self_presentation</data>
</edge>
