  <data key="d17">as "being" of substance and accident . Accordingly, "epikeia" is a part of justice taken in a general sense, for it is a kind of justice , as the Philosopher states (Ethic. v, 10). Wherefore it is evident that "epikeia" is a subjective part of justice ; and justice is predicated of it with prior</data>
